entry.title: Before Lahaina Fire, Hawaiian Electric Was Far Behind in Fixing Old Power Poles
entry.content: The utility regularly fell behind on plans to replace tens of thousands of utility poles at risk of failure and spent millions less on upgrades than it planned, a Wall Street Journal review of regulatory records found.
